<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3073> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3073" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Attempted to hinder Caepio's departure for Spain (Liv. Oxy. Per. 54). In revenge for Scipio's attempt while Censor to demote him to the aerarii, he prosecuted him and taunted him with his infelix lustrum (Cic. De Or. 2.258, 268; Gell. 2.20.6; 3.4.1; 4.17.1; 6.11.9; Fest. 362 L; cf. FOR 1.114-116, 237f.)." .
